No, there was some confusing with an issue that got an addition with a new bug report after it was solved and closed. I'm not sure this is a problem in geth 1.4.x.

@knocte, geth 1.4 has a new RPC implementation which is more strict. The old 1.3.6 accepted an address that was too short and filled missing bytes with 0. Geth 1.4 would return an error. In this case it looks like that you only supplied 4 bytes instead of all 40 bytes.

Based on the source in your report its hard to determine what the problem is and I don't have a Windows or mono installation available to try it. Could you trace it down to the actual RPC call and post the raw request that caused the error? Please check if the request contains an address that it is 40 bytes. This error is returned when the supplied address is not 40 bytes but only 4 bytes (`0xbb9b`)
